__NAME__ purpose
do not reparse Interchange output by default
__END__


__NAME__ synopsis
<group choice='plain'>
	<arg choice='plain'>0</arg>
	<arg choice='plain'>1</arg>
</group>
__END__


__NAME__ default
0
__END__


__NAME__ description
This &glos-pragma; disables default &glos-reparse; of Interchange output
from container tags.
</para><para>
Reparsing can, of course, still be requested using the
<literal>Reparse</literal> setting
in individual &glos-ITL; tag definition, or by providing the
universal <literal>reparse=1</literal> attribute to any container tag.
__END__


__NAME__ example: Enable no_default_reparse pragma page-wide
Put the following anywhere on your page:
<programlisting>
[pragma no_default_reparse]
</programlisting>
__END__

